Text.string: Vault Hunter! I wish I could give you the proper Jakobs welcome to Eden-6, but those COV devils are everywhere. Me and a few survivors are holed up in my family's lodge. Supplies are running low and we're surrounded. I need your help.
What a shot! You put a little dash-fire in that one! Been killin' since you was in the crib, I'm guessing.
You're driving 'em back! Just a few more, Vault Hunter!

Help yourself to some firearms. I salvaged what little I could from my father's personal collection, but he can't use 'em now. Those twin Calypso devils murdered him and took everything from me, and if you hadn't come along, I reckon I'd be in the mud too.
If my father was still breathin', he'd tell me to march right up to those devils and negotiate with the smokin' end of a Jakobs firearm. So that's exactly what we're gon' do.

See, that cult is holding Alistair in a prison called The Anvil. I already sent a team of mercenaries to break him out, but I ain't heard from them since. Rescue Alistair, and I'll get you that damn Vault Key. You in?
Yeah, sure. Been a while since I worked a prison break.
Oh, I am in. I am very much “in”.
Sure! Never been on the other side of a prison break before.
Prison break? Sure. Why not?
Now, I'm not worried about Meatslab biting it—he's more of a mountain than a man, and much angrier. But attention span ain't his strong suit, particularly when there's punches to be thrown.
Meatslab reports that the rescue is back on track! Well done, Vault Hunter!
Hmm, the team I sent in still isn't responding. Something must've happened. Get that gate open, Vault Hunter.
All right. The team's muscle, codename “Meatslab”, should be securing an escape route as we speak. He'll be near the prison's front gate. Find him, and get Alistair out of there alive.

Glad you're here! Things got complicated. I was waiting for the signal from our demolitions expert, but something went down. Must've been zealots or COV or... whatever we're calling 'em now. Name doesn't matter, as long as I get to hit 'em hard! Hit 'em real hard!
All right, more punchin' bags! Ha-HA!
I gotta get you to our demolitionist, Ti—right, uh, we're supposed to be using code names. “Crunk Bunny” needs your help. Follow me!
Hitting dudes. It's my job and my hobby!
Attention, everyone. Vault Thieves are here. Kill them while I question machine man about the Vault Key! Stay bloodthirsty!
Come out, come out, wherever you are!
Move and you die.||I will now read the crimes of the condemned.||You kidnapped my...

Okay, look, here's the deal. They're keeping Hammylocks in max security, and there's a big old door that needs blowin' off, heh, but, uh... but... shiz got complicated, and some bandits TOOK MY BOMB!||I'm okay! I'm okay, I'm okay. So! Do me a flava, and grab some toppings for this bomb-ass pizza I'm cookin' up.

I bet you like, “Hey Tina, why you call it pizza?” 'Cause you can deliver a pizza anywhere, shorty. And people like, “Oh, is this a pizza? Splendid. Now, scurry on. I shant be tipping you.” Then I'm like, “Here's a tip. Kaboom, sucka!”||Pizzas open doors, that's—that's my point.
Okay, I needs a bottle of nitroglycerin, which I calls “sauce”. Can't make a bomb-ass pizza without sauce!
Ohhhohohoho! Saucy-sauuuuce, hoo-hoo! Hammylock's gonna LOVE this pizza. 'Cause it smells like freedom. And nitroglcyerin, so, you know... hold your breath.
Nice! This bomb's gonna be, as they say in the bizness... the shizness.
Y'know, some people don't like onion, but I just tell 'em, “Never say that to me again.” Onion is queen! It's QUEEN!
Hohhhoho, yeah. Ahh, that's a good onion.
Ham. In honor of my man... the man... Sir Hammylock.
BOOM! Hamtown!
Well done, my plucky young assistant. Now—meet me at the gate outside max security, and we shall assemble this pizza bomb for my man Hammylock!
Ooohoohoohoo, this is gonna be good! We gonna put that shiz in the oven and BAKE!
Here it is!
Take it! Take it, take it, take-it-takeittakeittktktktiktik!
The box. In, in my hand. It's... it's for you. Take it. Take it!
Please, Vaulty Vault. Take... me... pizza box.
[singing] Takin' the box, it's what you got to do. Takin' the box, takin', takin' my HEART from a box with a bomb in it.
Now deliver that pizza to my sniper man, who I like to call “The Bird Man”. Cawww!
That's not my codename!
You right, you right—uhhhhh, what was it, again? “Boo-boo Choco-do”? “Zapper Clapper”? “Hurdy-Birdy Gurdy Man”? “Bird Boy”? “Sad Bird Man”? “Bird Brain”? Somethin' with bird.
Just “Sniper”. Come on, I can't hold out forever!
Unhand me, vandal! I don't know where that blasted Vault Key is, I swear!
Rrgh—damn you to hell!
Tina, where's that pizza?
My delivery specialist is on the way, boo boo! Okay? Keep cool.
Maintain ECHO silence! Always wanted to say that, heh-heh! Ooooh. More chumps! Awesome!
I don't know, I swear!
Vault Hunter—secure the bridge!
Delivery is on schedule! Hey, screw code names. How's our exit, Brick?
Escape route is clear! Tina, you ready?
Oooh! It's time! [singing] It's time, it's time, it's pizza delivery TIIIIME! Vaulty-Vault! It's time! Deliver that boom pie!
Now shoot that pizza. Do it. Do it! Do it, do it, doitdoitdoiddlddtdtdtdldt!
Felt that one from here!
Tina! Did you have to make it so damn strong?
Gahahahaaaa! Ahhhh, yeah, I did.
Excellent, a Vault Hunter!
Good luuuuuuck!
Ah, well met! Now, if you could just lower the cage!
My thanks, Vault Hunter! I am not too worse for wear, all things considered! I am glad that Wainwright sent you.
I shall rest here a moment and meet you back at the lodge. Now that my safety is secured, I imagine Wainwright has already set plans in motion to retake his family namesake.
Whoo! A wellspring of heartwine sprung right outta that bastard's throat! That was a damn fine shot, if I do say so myself—and I do!
Not gonna talk? Then I take machine man's metal arm!
If you no talk, I do this!
Whoever kills the Vault Thief gets to be my torture assistant!
Kill the Vault Thief. I'm not done interrogating machine man!
Whoever kills the Vault Thief gets an Eridium-tier membership. So go kill!
Want front row seats to the grand opening of the Great Vault?! Then kill the Vault Thief!
Kill the Vault Thief NOW! You don't want to see me angry!
There's a Vault Thief in our prison. Somebody stop them!
I'm not done interrogating this heretic. Someone else is gonna have to kill the Vault Thief!
I'm getting angry. Kill the Vault Thief, or I'll kill you all myself!
Kill the Vault Thief NOW!
We're almost there. And trust me, you don't want to keep Crunk Bunny waitin'!
It's an ambush! Lets beat 'em together, slab!
Unhand my hand this instant, you vile specimen!
I escaped with my life, but they captured my partner Alistair Hammerlock. Those devils are holding him as leverage until I cough up the Vault Key. Which is also why you're here, I presume?
Yo Meatslab, you comin', man? I got eyes on max security, but COV's heading my way!
Hold on, Bird Man. I got you, fam!
Nice fighting! Usually I'm a solo brawler, but that duet was baller! I gotta go help out our sniper. You meet up with Crunk Bunny!
Later!

Ooh! Also, we ARE gonna need a detonator for that bomb-ass bomb, my boo. Uh, I—I call it “ham”, in, uh, pizza-bomb talk. Heh. And I know where you can get that sweet, sweet piggy. You gotta kill one of them boom-kiddos. The ones holding the bombs? They my favorite.
Yo, Vaulty Vault Hunter! Official Hammylock rescuer: that's you now, boo.

Tannis says the Vault down on Promethea was somehow connected to one on Eden-6? If the Calypsos want to get their hands on that Vault, those monsters are gonna have to go through us. Luckily, we have a friend in the area.
Sir Hammerlock? With pleasure! I'll bet he can't wait to hear about my many adventures.
(yelling as they attack Wainwright, shooting, etc.)

Hey, how's paradise? Thought the home of “Jakobs” would be less... ehh, I want to say... swamp-assy? Dangerous place, Eden-6. Reminds me of home. Anyway, the Maliwan sponsorship was a bust, but we did take a page from Katagawa's murder diary. This time, I just BAMF'd right in at dinnertime and leeched the CEO of Jakobs! Boom! Done! Installed a loyal puppet instead, and she is a trip. Real ice-queen, y'know? She manages the books, keeps the locals in line. It's just nice to see another rich bitch in charge, you know! You know.
Hyah!
My name is Wainwright Jakobs, but I'm afraid my name's all I have left. Those devils have taken everything else. Well, come on in.
Now, I should warn you... “Crunk Bunny” is a damn prodigy with explosives, but... how do I say this... she's nuttier than squirrel shit.
You moved. Whatever!
There's gotta be a sauce storage room somewhere, shorty.
Go get them wires, shorty. We call 'em onion strings in the biz! Long wires make the bomb fizz-fizz oh so right.
Ayyyy, new promotion! Ehhh? You're movin' up in this chain, my man. Corporate ladder and whatnot. Get it, you got this!
Vault Hunter. That chain must have a weakness!
Surely, there's something you can shoot to lower the cage!
Are you feeling unwell, Vault Hunter? Surely you're up for some shooting, yes?
To lower the cage, find the chain's weakpoint!
You found Meatslab? All right! Let's get this rescue back on track.

Now, as to my incarceration. I'm sorry to say the one who traded me to those wretched Calypso Twins in exchange for the Jakobs Corporation... THAT foul creature is my own sister, Aurelia Hammerlock. As to why she sold me to the cult. Well, simply put... she despises me. She always has. There is no stronger bond than family, and when that bond is broken, no greater source of pain.
I got you, VH!
Got the drop pod ready for ya, VH.
The Jakobs family has controlled Eden-6 for centuries. There were rumors of a Vault, but not even Typhon DeLeon himself was able to locate it. Perhaps this Wainwright Jakobs knows something.
Aw, hell yeah, another Vault Hunter! This job just keeps getting better! Help me beat down some bandits—then we'll talk.
Badass! Now let's gab, slab!
Listen, VH. Lil's already lost enough. We all have—but there ain't anyone who can take on the COV but us. You be careful down there, hon. Watch yer ass, all right?
Vault Hunter—you just saved my damn life, and I am in your debt. Let's talk.
They call me the doorman! And Meatslab! I'm a lot of things.
This way!

Those craven zealots! Jakobs Corporation has survived for three hundred years, but these COV devils have spread across the system like a damn plague. All under the orders of those rat-bastard Calypsos. They murdered my father because he wouldn't hand over our Vault, and now they've come for me!
Damn these devils! If they want to die for their so-called gods, please oblige them, Vault Hunter!
The Great Vault BECKONS! Jakobs will BLEED!
Yup.
That's right.
It is.
Bingo.

That Vault has been a family secret for generations—we didn't want our fair paradise to be torn asunder like what happened to Promethea and Pandora. Where there's a Vault, there's always a war. But right now, I've more pressing concerns than my family legacy. Alistair Hammerlock, love of my life—if they kill him, I got nothing left.
Those zealots are like saurians in heat. When those lustful lizards start matin', they go so blind with desire they don't know whether to bite or bust.
These zealots really itch my ass. Help me give 'em a good scratchin', would ya?
Claptrap, get Hammerlock on vidscreen.
That's the town of Reliance—or, used to be. Home to our finest gunsmiths! Central to our logging operations, too. At least my father's not alive to see it's fallen to those bandit devils.
You'll find the lodge at the peak. We'll fight these devils off best we can, but I suggest you hurry!
Glad you're here. Not sure how much longer we could've held those COV zealots off.
As long as I can hold a Jakobs shotgun in my hand, I ain't handing over Eden-6 without a fight! Come at me, you mud-sucking bastards!
Still catchin' up, huh, Vault Thief? Here, this'll slow you down.
I got this for you!
You just keep going, don'tcha, Vault Thief? Have you considered, I dunno, laying down and dying? Seemed to work for your Siren friend. Haven't heard any complaints from her.
I'll hold down the fort and protect what's left of my people. Good luck.
Damn, you're huge.
You're like... a mountain of muscle.
Meatslab, I presume?
You remind me of my brother! He was a biggun' too.
Heh. Yeah.

Lilith. Wainwright Jakobs, at your service. I'm sorry to report that those COV zealots have kidnapped Hammerlock. And it seems they're here for me!||—One step closer and I'll whup ya with lead! I'll emblazon my family crest on your craven ass!
“Oh no, more guards!”
More friends of yours to kill. Fun!
That big dumbass looks tasty!
I hope Hammerlock's all right.
Ay yo, bay-bay!
What's up? So, we freeing this Hammerlock guy or what?
So? We doing this thing or what? Heard this Hammerlock guy needs our help.
Wainwright told me to save Hammerlock.
“Ay yo baby” yourself! Came to free Hammerlock.
Full disclosure, it is actually a bomb. It's a... it's a big ol' bomb.
I know this place got the toppings I need somewhere, and Tina's got a special recipe, extra spicy.
Well done, my plucky young assistant! Now let's meet back up and we shall assemble this pizza bomb for my sweet man Hammylock.

And, for doin' such a good job, I'm gonna promote you! You're my pizza delivery specialist now. Ha! You earned it, boo. Just don't let it get cold, and DO NOT DROP IT! And also, don't try to eat it like those dumbass bandits, okay?
Looks like the the COV are already on Eden-6. Vault Hunter, meet up with Wainwright Jakobs and find out what's going on down there.
I got you, Bird Boy.
On my way to you, Zapper Clapper.
I am en route to you, Hurdy-Birdy Gurdy Man.
On my way, Boo-Boo Choco-Do!
Thanks, Vault Hunter! See you soon!
Watch out!
Give that monster a good thrashing!
Save me, Vault Hunter!
I'm free!
Awww, yeah!
All right!
Our job here is done! Catch you later, Vaulty-Vault! B-team OUT!
Family? Tch. All I need is Iron Bear.
I haven't seen my family in ages. Not sure they'd even recognize me.
Family is not blood, but who you hunt with. My beasts are my kin.
Family's rough. I know how you feel. My brothers tried to kill me loads of times. Look who outlived them all, though!
Where is the Vault Key?
Hmm. Indeed.
